==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: modulated
<hw>modulated</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <fld>(Electronics)</fld> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Having either amplitude, intensity, frequency, or phase altered at
intervals to represent information to be transmitted; -- of the carrier
wave of a radio signal transmitted from one device to another for the
purpose of conveying information. Opposite of
<ant>unmodulated</ant>.</def> [Narrower terms: <stype>frequency
modulated</stype>; <stype>amplitude modulated</stype>]⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>altered in volume as well as tone or
pitch.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Modulation</ent>⟦br⟧
